text.tspan: All you need is a single brand color, and a passion for
learning how to create beautiful and accessible designs.
Each color is a degree on a 360° color wheel. 0° is red, 120° is green, 240° is blue.
The intensity and vibrance of a color. 0% is fully grey, 100% is no grey at all.
How light or dark a color is. 0% is completely black, 100% is completely white.
Find out what the hue value for your brand color is.
Find the color that is closest to your brand color in the wheel at the top of this page.
A good accent color is one of the two or three colors directly opposite it on the wheel.
Keep your hue value the same, and the saturation level at 100% (except grey, S = 0%).
Then change the lightness value to match the shades shown in the palettes on the right.
